THE father who poisoned his four kids has died. According to his father-in-law, the man died in hospital on Friday, 10 June. The father 40-year-old from Ratanda in Heidelberg poisoned his four kids and three died. The mkhulu said the 11 year old who survived the poison is still in hospital and is doing well. He couldn’t say much yesterday as he said he was on his way to the hospital to understand what happened. The incident which shocked Mzansi had people rallying around the mother to help her bury her kids. The father had allegedly given the kids poisoned energy drink before leaving for school on 26 May. The energy drink was laced with Galephirime. Four drank but the fifth boy refused to drink it. Two of the boys, Katleho and Lehlohonolo Khoabane aged 16 and 13 respectively, were pupils at Khanya-Lesedi High school and while six-year-old Teboho Ngcongwane was a pupil at Ratanda Primary school. After feeding his kids and his dog a poison infused drink, he tried to commit suicide but didn’t succeed. He was admitted to hospital where he died on Friday. His three boys were buried on 4 June. Local business people, taxi associations, the local municipality, local funeral parlour and the Gauteng Education Department joined hands to ensure the boys were buried in a dignified manner.